# Sensor Setup

1. Install the 2 Picos one on each board
2. Connect one Pico USB power to your computer USB 2.0 port (Not 3.0!) and to the Pico
3. Wire up the 2 boards with the correct power pin setup ![power pin setup](../images/rpi_dev-starting_schematic.png)
4. Wire up the sensor to the target board with the pinout ![pinout](../images/rpi_sensor_schematic.png). This looks like:

- Pico installed on the Board ![pico installed](../images/Pico_On_Board.jpeg)

- Additional jumpers connected to the Pico ![jumper_connections](../images/Sensor_Jumpers.jpeg)

- Sensor Connected to board ![board connected](../images/Sensor_To_Board.jpeg)

- Sensor Connected to Pico ![Pico connected](../images/Sensor_Pico.jpeg)

- Sensor and Power Connected ![power connected](../images/Sensor_And_Power_Circuit.jpeg)

